Emergency brake assistance is now mandatory
As has taken place with the anti-lock system of ABS brakes and as will be done with the ESP stability control, emergency braking support systems will be a mandatory element on European cars.
They are already compulsory on newly registered passenger cars and light commercial vehicles, while for the rest of the vehicles a period of failure has been set until the end of February 2011.
The measure, imposed by the European Union, aims to strengthen pedestrian protection, although, by its mode of action, it can also help to avoid many rear impacts.
The emergency brake assistant acts by increasing the pressure on the brakes in the event of an emergency detected by the system thanks to the driver's kick.
But the latter does not always keep up the pressure until the end.
